Tshisekedi will sign the treaty before President Uhuru Kenyatta who is the current chair of the bloc. The DRC was admitted as the community’s seventh member on March 29 after approval by EAC heads of state. Leaders of the member states are also expected at the ceremony where they will unveil a new map of the bloc to include DRC. Kenyatta and Tshisekedi are also expected to sign co-operation agreements. --BBC—